	"description": "This template calculates inflation based on several inflation index data sets. \n\nNote that this template defaults to calculating the inflation of Consumer Price Index values: staples, workers' rent, small service bills (doctor's costs, train tickets). For inflating capital expenses, government expenses, or the personal wealth and expenditure of the rich, the US-GDP or UK-GDP indexes should be used, which calculate inflation based on the [[gross domestic product]] (GDP) for the [[:en:United States|United States]] and [[:en:United Kingdom|United Kingdom]], respectively."
}
</templatedata>

